about why he thought

00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:17.466
he wasn't getting those jobs,
it was insane to hear about some

00:01:17.466 --> 00:01:19.340
of the things that were
going on, things such

00:01:19.340 --> 00:01:23.180
as, oh, some companies
didn't necessarily

00:01:23.180 --> 00:01:25.820
think that disclosure
was a good idea.

00:01:25.820 --> 00:01:29.870
Some companies
didn't think that,

00:01:29.870 --> 00:01:32.660
looking at the bottom line,
that reasonable accommodations

00:01:32.660 --> 00:01:36.770
for me would be a
little bit outrageous.

00:01:36.770 --> 00:01:40.970
And I'm happy to say he now
has a job today at Ford Motor

00:01:40.970 --> 00:01:42.680
Company.

00:01:42.680 --> 00:01:45.230
But it took a very,
very long time

00:01:45.230 --> 00:01:50.190
for this man who grew up with
many challenges due to autism.

00:01:50.190 --> 00:01:52.430
And this is actually
something I deal

00:01:52.430 --> 00:01:55.460
with almost every single
day in our community.

00:01:55.460 --> 00:01:58.490
Today, as a eight-year
professional speaker,

00:01:58.490 --> 00:02:01.670
I travel the country talking
about autism inclusion

00:02:01.670 --> 00:02:05.030
and trying to become the
best version of yourself.

00:02:05.030 --> 00:02:08.509
So my presentation topic
today, the ROI benefits

00:02:08.509 --> 00:02:11.000
of hiring people with autism
and other special needs

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:12.750
in the workplace--

00:02:12.750 --> 00:02:14.570
some of the things
that you truly, truly

00:02:14.570 --> 00:02:16.280
need to know about
our community,

00:02:16.280 --> 00:02:20.510
and I'll share about this a
little bit later, but in terms

00:02:20.510 --> 00:02:24.620
of the autism community, over
80% of adults in the United

00:02:24.620 --> 00:02:27.590
States are currently
unemployed or underemployed.

00:02:27.590 --> 00:02:31.280
And now I can say, based on
overcoming many obstacles,

00:02:31.280 --> 00:02:37.730
through over five different
therapies for almost 15 years

00:02:37.730 --> 00:02:40.610
of my life in occupational,
physical, speech, music,

00:02:40.610 --> 00:02:43.460
and theater therapy, I've
been able to overcome

00:02:43.460 --> 00:02:46.760
many of my obstacles
today to pursue a career

00:02:46.760 --> 00:02:47.990
in professional speaking.

00:02:47.990 --> 00:02:50.450
It's given me the
wonderful opportunity

00:02:50.450 --> 00:02:52.760
to become an
international speaker.

00:02:52.760 --> 00:02:55.790
I had the opportunity to
write two bestselling books,

00:02:55.790 --> 00:02:57.590
focus on special need parenting.

00:02:57.590 --> 00:02:59.890
The first book, "Defining
Autism From the Heart,"

00:02:59.890 --> 00:03:03.800
