growing up with autism,

00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:44.360
I grew up wanting to
be the next Larry Bird,

00:07:44.360 --> 00:07:46.670
and I have no vertical
leap for the life of me.

00:07:46.670 --> 00:07:49.680
So that was kind
of a difficulty.

00:07:49.680 --> 00:07:53.630
However, I really got involved
with sport management.

00:07:53.630 --> 00:07:56.600
So one of my first internships
ever was CBS Sports.

00:07:56.600 --> 00:07:59.810
And I majored at Seton Hall
University in sports management

00:07:59.810 --> 00:08:04.540
and I was hoping to pursue a
career in the sports world.

00:08:04.540 --> 00:08:07.250
Once graduating
from college, I had

00:08:07.250 --> 00:08:10.760
offers to work with many
different sport-related

00:08:10.760 --> 00:08:13.820
organizations in
my tri-state area.

00:08:13.820 --> 00:08:18.200
And I really fell in
love with my mentees.

00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:20.600
I came out for the first
time about having an autism

00:08:20.600 --> 00:08:22.820
diagnosis because
today I'm considered

00:08:22.820 --> 00:08:25.320
to have a, quote unquote,
"invisible" disability.

00:08:25.320 --> 00:08:29.030
Many people I meet to this day
say, Kerry, you have autism?

00:08:29.030 --> 00:08:30.650
You don't look like
you have autism.

00:08:30.650 --> 00:08:33.990
And I'm like, oh, that's an
interesting way of putting it.

00:08:33.990 --> 00:08:36.350
And I have to tell them
that I will always have

00:08:36.350 --> 00:08:37.919
autism for the rest of my life.

00:08:37.919 --> 00:08:40.760
But I truly fell in
love with mentoring kids

00:08:40.760 --> 00:08:44.250
with disabilities as they
transition to adulthood.

00:08:44.250 --> 00:08:46.700
So I pursued a career
in public speaking.

00:08:46.700 --> 00:08:49.250
And one of the
biggest things we--

00:08:49.250 --> 00:08:51.080
one of the biggest
reasons why we also

00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:53.840
decided to do this change
was because we realized

00:08:53.840 --> 00:08:56.690
that many, many individuals
with disabilities

00:08:56.690 --> 00:08:59.660
were truly still not
being able to be engaged

00:08:59.660 --> 00:09:01.350
with the world around them.

00:09:01.350 --> 00:09:03.980
So I wanted to share with all
of you really quickly a video

00:09:03.980 --> 00:09:07.040
where we're trying to make the
world that more inclusive place

00:09:07.040 --> 00:09:08.180
for everyone to live.

